==German==
===Etymology===
{{OHG.}} [[turi]], from Germanic ''*duri-'', from Indo-European ''*dhur-, *dhwer-''.  Cognate with Middle Dutch [[dore]] (Dutch [[deur]]), Old Norse [[dyrr]] (Swedish [[dörr]]).  The Germanic word also existed in different stem-endings: ''*dora-'' (German [[Tor]], Old English [[dor]]), ''*duru-'' (Old English [[duru]]).

